text: Sajjad Ganjzadeh (, also Romanized as "Sajjād Ganjzādeh"; born 4 January 1992) is an Iranian karateka. Competing in the above 84 kg kumite division he won gold medals at the 2014 and 2016 world championships, 2013 and 2017 Asian championships, and 2018 Asian Games. == References == Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:Iranian male karateka Category:Asian Games gold medalists for Iran Category:Asian Games medalists in karate Category:Karateka at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Karateka at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games Category:World Games silver medalists Category:Competitors at the 2017 World Games Category:World Games medalists in karate Category:Asian Games competitors for Iran
